OL,3,CUkrainian prisoners offered release
OL,4,Cbut must join military in return
OL,6,FThe new recruitment drive, approved by
OL,7,Fthe Ukrainian parliament in a
OL,8,Fcontroversial bill, has already seen
OL,9,Fmore than 3,000 prisoners released on
OL,10,Fparole and assigned to military units.
OL,12,FAnother 27,000 could be eligible for
OL,13,Fthe new military draft, the Ukrainian
OL,14,FJustice Ministry says.
OL,16,FErnest Volvach, 27, is serving a two-
OL,17,Fyear sentence for robbery at a penal
OL,18,Fcolony in Ukraine's Dnipropetrovsk
OL,19,Fregion, he told AP he wants to join
OL,20,Fthe programme to "do something for
OL,21,FUkraine".
