OL,3,CUkrainian prisoners offered release
OL,4,Cbut must join military in return
OL,6,FAfter completing his sentence in a
OL,7,Fyear, a 30-year-old inmate, who
OL,8,Fcurrently works as a riveter at a
OL,9,Fpenal colony, plans to volunteer but
OL,10,Frefuses to do so currently due to the
OL,11,Flack of home leave under the parole
OL,12,Fprogramme.
OL,14,FParoled inmate Mykhailo, 29, told AP:
OL,15,F"I decided to sign up for the
OL,16,FUkrainian Volunteer Army because I
OL,17,Fhave a family at home, children,
OL,18,Fparents... I will be more useful in
OL,19,Fthe war."
